HAMISH: Look, you did good.

39:32.160 --> 39:36.040
I had my doubts, but, uh, you
really brought this thing home.

39:36.120 --> 39:38.873
I had a few breaks.
Don't do that.

39:38.960 --> 39:41.839
Take praise and turn it
into something else.

39:41.920 --> 39:43.115
You're right.
I'm sorry.

39:43.200 --> 39:44.713
And don't apologize.

39:44.800 --> 39:46.518
You still got a few
rungs left to climb.

39:46.600 --> 39:49.240
You're not gonna get there
saying you're sorry.

39:49.320 --> 39:51.470
Got it.
Thank you, sir.

39:52.720 --> 39:54.119
(DOOR CREAKING)

39:55.160 --> 39:56.309
I did.

39:56.640 --> 39:58.472
I worked hard night and day
to get this done,

39:58.560 --> 40:00.358
I don't mind
telling you.

40:00.440 --> 40:02.716
Which is why I was thinking,
for this setup in Fargo,

40:02.800 --> 40:04.552
I'd like to handpick
a few men...

40:04.640 --> 40:06.711
No, no, no.
That's the day-to-day stuff.

40:06.840 --> 40:08.274
We got a team for that.

40:08.360 --> 40:11.876
Asset managers, mid-level
and below. Drones, really.

40:11.960 --> 40:13.394
They've already been
deployed.

40:13.480 --> 40:16.677
The real oversight of the new
northern territories...

40:16.760 --> 40:19.991
Well, that happens right here,
in this building.

40:21.000 --> 40:23.116
Which is where
you want me.

40:23.200 --> 40:25.237
Assuming you don't wanna be
a grunt your entire life.

40:25.360 --> 40:27.033
No. Of course not.

40:27.680 --> 40:29.512
Good.
Then pay attention.

40:34.800 --> 40:38.839
It's 9:00 to 5:00 mostly, but
management rewards initiative,

40:38.920 --> 40:42.436
So, nights, weekends,
whatever gets the job done.

40:42.520 --> 40:45.399
You'll be working closely with
the, uh, accounting department,

40:45.480 --> 40:47.471
looking for ways to
optimize revenue.

40:47.560 --> 40:51.793
Shorter shipping routes, less
palms to grease, that kind of thing.

40:51.880 --> 40:53.075
The accounting
department.

40:53.160 --> 40:57.950
Yeah, and this whole, uh,
Western thing. That's gotta go.

40:58.320 --> 41:02.871
Get something gray or pinstriped with
a white shirt, (STUTTERS) a real tie.

41:02.960 --> 41:05.110
And cut your hair,
okay?

41:05.200 --> 41:07.555
The '70s are over, for
Christ's sake. (CHUCKLES)

41:10.040 --> 41:12.998
See, I thought, well...

41:13.880 --> 41:15.951
In the old days, when a
guy conquered a place...

41:16.040 --> 41:17.633
You want the old days?

41:17.720 --> 41:19.313
Go work in a coal mine.

41:19.400 --> 41:21.232
This is the future.

41:22.080 --> 41:25.118
Look, you and I got off
on the wrong foot,

41:25.200 --> 41:28.113
but you seem like a good kid,
so let me give you a tip.

41:28.200 --> 41:32.080
The sooner you realize there's
only one business left in the world...

41:32.400 --> 41:35.438
The money business,
just ones and zeros,

41:35.520 --> 41:37.079
the better off
you're gonna be.

41:38.600 --> 41:40.432
Sir, believe me,
I'm an earner.

41:40.560 --> 41:41.789
Yeah, yeah,
but listen to me,

41:41.880 --> 41:44.679
I'm not talking about
busting heads for collections.

41:44.760 --> 41:47.593
I'm talking about
profit and loss...

41:47.680 --> 41:49.239
Infrastructure.

41:49.960 --> 41:51.633
See, (CLEARS THROAT)

41:51.720 --> 41:55.554
Iast year, Donahue in
the western branch...

41:55.640 --> 41:57.677
He rejiggered
the mail room,

41:57.760 --> 42:02.072
ended up saving a million
