45:56.360 --> 45:59.990
And when I went over there
the first time...

46:01.920 --> 46:03.433
I went in your office.

46:06.320 --> 46:07.515
Ah...

46:09.280 --> 46:10.634
So, uh...

46:12.960 --> 46:14.359
Well, okay.

46:18.360 --> 46:19.509
So...

46:21.080 --> 46:22.514
(SIGHS, MUTTERS)

46:24.040 --> 46:28.193
After your mother died,
I got to feeling pretty low.

46:29.040 --> 46:30.360
We all did.

46:31.480 --> 46:34.552
And I took... Well, you
remember, I took some time off.

46:35.040 --> 46:36.872
And I started thinking...

46:38.080 --> 46:40.071
Which I know
is dangerous...

46:41.520 --> 46:42.715
But, you know,

46:45.440 --> 46:46.794
the things I've seen...

46:47.680 --> 46:48.875
In the war,

46:51.720 --> 46:53.870
and at home,
on the job...

46:54.640 --> 46:56.836
So much
senselessness.

46:57.320 --> 47:00.631
Violence, you know? (STUTTERS)
And I got to thinking about...

47:02.160 --> 47:04.151
About miscommunication.

47:04.960 --> 47:07.429
Like how, isn't that
the root of it?

47:08.880 --> 47:13.238
Conflict, war... Doesn't it
all come down to language?

47:14.840 --> 47:17.753
Right? The words we say
and the words we hear,

47:17.840 --> 47:19.592
which aren't always
the same thing.

47:19.680 --> 47:22.911
So, I thought, you know, what
if there was one language?

47:23.960 --> 47:28.511
A universal language of
symbols, 'cause pictures,

47:29.280 --> 47:31.920
to my mind, (STUTTERS)
are clearer than words.

47:35.200 --> 47:37.191
So, that's what that is?

47:37.920 --> 47:39.433
In your office.

47:41.440 --> 47:43.431
You're making
your own language.

47:46.040 --> 47:48.953
Well, it sounds crazy when
you say it out loud, I know.

47:50.520 --> 47:51.715
But...

47:54.320 --> 47:57.950
You know, when we see
a box with a roof on it,

47:58.520 --> 48:01.160
well, everyone knows
that means home.

48:01.240 --> 48:05.473
